title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theater on 1980-10-04
lineage: Cassette (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6MHz) > Sound Forge 13 Pro (WAV 24-bit/96k) > Adobe Audition 2020 > Samplitude Pro X5 Suite (24-bit/48k) > FLAC/24
description:
Set I
Acoustic Set

Deep Elem Blues
The Race Is On
It Must Have Been The Roses
Monkey & The Engineer
Rosalie McFall
Dark Hollow
To Lay Me Down
On The Road Again
Oh Babe It Ain't No Lie >
Ripple
Set II
Electric Set 1

Alabama Getaway >
Greatest Story Ever Told
Candyman
Mama Tried >
Mexicali Blues
High Time
Passenger
Althea
Little Red Rooster

Electric Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger >

Estimated Prophet >

Drums >
Space >
Not Fade Away >
Wharf Rat >
I Need A Miracle >
Johnny B. Goode

Encore:
Uncle John's Band >
One More Saturday Night
Comment
Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar

reviews.review_text: Warfield Dead - 1980. Show is from 1980, not 1989.  Part of the famous 3-set Warfield shows, 1st set being acoustic.  Some tracks made it to "Dead Set" LP.  Nice soundboard!
